President Jacob Zuma on Monday, conveyed a message of condolence to the Iranian government after the passing of former president Ayatollah Akbar Hashemi Rafsanjani, the department of international relations and cooperation said Rafsanjani, aged 82, passed away on Sunday. South Africa acknowledges President Rafsanjani s pioneering spirit in establishing stronger trade and political ties with African countries and South Africa in particular during his term as the President of Iran, Zuma said in a statement. Zuma said the people of South Africa share the loss of the Iranian people and stand with them in this time of grief and mourning. African News Agency For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.